AdminChecks.Grist allows for very powerful formulas,: Grist allows for very powerful formulas, using Python. We recommend setting the environment variable GRIST_SANDBOX_FLAVOR to gvisor if your hardware supports it (most will), to run formulas in each document within a sandbox isolated from other documents and isolated from the network.
AdminChecks.Grist has a small built-in health check: Grist has a small built-in health check often used when running it as a container.
AdminChecks.Requests arriving to Grist should have a: Requests arriving to Grist should have an accurate Host header. This is essential when GRIST_SERVE_SAME_ORIGIN is set.
AdminChecks.This boot page should not be too easy to: This boot page should not be too easy to access. Either turn it off when configuration is ok (by unsetting GRIST_BOOT_KEY) or make GRIST_BOOT_KEY long and cryptographically secure.
AdminChecks.Websocket connections need HTTP 1.1 and: Websocket connections need HTTP 1.1 and the ability to pass a few extra headers in order to work. Sometimes a reverse proxy can interfere with these requirements.
AdminChecks.It is good practice not to run Grist as: It is good practice not to run Grist as the root user.
AdminChecks.The main page of Grist should be availab: The main page of Grist should be available.
